{
  "answer": "The following works in the corpus mention one or more specific Indian rivers (primarily the Ganges/Ganga, Yamunā/Yamuna, and Sarasvatī, along with the associated Driṣadvatī). No mentions were found for rivers such as the Indus, Brahmaputra, Godāvarī, Narmadā, or Kāverī.[^1]\n\n**Āṅgirasa Smṛti** (unknown-angirasa-smrti-2bf9d1): Mentions the Ganges (bank thereof).[^2]\n\n**Nouveau traité d'économie: VOL I** by Charles Dunoyer (charles-dunoyer-nouveau-traite-deconomie-vol-i-6da8ce): Mentions the Ganges (as a geographical boundary of regions).[^3][^4]\n\n**Traité de Législation: VOL II** by Charles Comte (charles-comte-traite-de-legislation-vol-ii-20331d): Mentions the Ganges (as a geographical boundary).[^5]\n\n**Viṣṇu Smṛti** (unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8): Multiple mentions of the Ganges (its waters for ritual immersion, etc.) and Yamunā (its bank as a sacred site).[^6]\n\n**Manusmṛti** (unknown-manusmrti-347b76): Mentions Sarasvatī and Driṣadvatī (defining the Brahmāvarta region); Sarasvatī (in expiatory rites); and Ganga (in a warning about false witness).[^7][^8]\n\n**Vīramitrodaya** (unknown-viramitrodaya-d4b632): Mentions Gaṅgā and Yamunā (in a compound illustrating grammar).[^9]\n\n[^1]: Based on searches for \"Ganges\", \"Ganga\", \"Yamuna\", \"Indus\", \"Brahmaputra\", \"Godavari\", \"Narmada\", \"Kaveri\", and \"Sarasvati\" across English translations.\n\n[^2]: Āṅgirasa Smṛti, [Chapter 1, paragraph](/works/unknown-angirasa-smrti-2bf9d1/01/translation/#p-543a9d).\n\n[^3]: Nouveau traité d'économie: VOL I, [Chapter 2, paragraph](/works/charles-dunoyer-nouveau-traite-deconomie-vol-i-6da8ce/02-i-influence-de-la-race-sur-la-liberte/translation/#p-6ac2b8).\n\n[^4]: Nouveau traité d'économie: VOL I, [Chapter 3, paragraph](/works/charles-dunoyer-nouveau-traite-deconomie-vol-i-6da8ce/03-ii-influence-des-circonstances-exterieures-sur-la-/translation/#p-1f97b0).\n\n[^5]: Traité de Législation: VOL II, [Chapter 3, paragraph](/works/charles-comte-traite-de-legislation-vol-ii-20331d/03-des-diverses-especes-ou-varietes-dont-se-compose-l/translation/#p-f0c315).\n\n[^6]: Viṣṇu Smṛti, [Chapter 19, paragraph](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/19/translation/#p-eaf423) (Ganges); also Chapters 20, 23, 64, 85 (Ganges and Yamunā banks).\n\n[^7]: Manusmṛti, [Chapter 2, paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/02/translation/#p-a9e644).\n\n[^8]: Manusmṛti, [Chapter 8, paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/08/translation/#p-803bc3) (Ganga and Sarasvatī); also Chapter 12.\n\n[^9]: Vīramitrodaya, [Chapter 1, paragraph](/works/unknown-viramitrodaya-d4b632/01/translation/#p-4c32c7).",
